<dec f='linux-5.3.1/include/net/cfg80211.h' l='7184' type='void cfg80211_shutdown_all_interfaces(struct wiphy * wiphy)'/>
<doc f='linux-5.3.1/include/net/cfg80211.h' l='7172'>/**
 * cfg80211_shutdown_all_interfaces - shut down all interfaces for a wiphy
 * @wiphy: the wiphy to shut down
 *
 * This function shuts down all interfaces belonging to this wiphy by
 * calling dev_close() (and treating non-netdev interfaces as needed).
 * It shouldn&apos;t really be used unless there are some fatal device errors
 * that really can&apos;t be recovered in any other way.
 *
 * Callers must hold the RTNL and be able to deal with callbacks into
 * the driver while the function is running.
 */</doc>
